subject: Fix common misspellings
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-23 14:04:11.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/first_patch.rst'], 'message': 'Fix common misspellings

Wikipedia's list of common misspellings [1] has a machine-readable
version.  This patch fixes those misspellings mentioned in the list
which don't have multiple right variants (as e.g. "accension", which can
be both "accession" and "ascension"), such misspellings are left
untouched.  The list of changes was manually re-checked for false
positives.

[1] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Lists_of_common_misspellings/For_machines

Change-Id: I961e9cbf27eb39461148f58dc6e8bdc1c9599541
Signed-off-by: Martin Kletzander <mkletzan@redhat.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Fix common misspellings

Wikipedia's list of common misspellings [1] has a machine-readable
version.  This patch fixes those misspellings mentioned in the list
which don't have multiple right variants (as e.g. "accension", which can
be both "accession" and "ascension"), such misspellings are left
untouched.  The list of changes was manually re-checked for false
positives.

[1] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Lists_of_common_misspellings/For_machines

Change-Id: I961e9cbf27eb39461148f58dc6e8bdc1c9599541
Signed-off-by: Martin Kletzander <mkletzan@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Removing Windows drivers for no reported CI

CI deadlines were set and pushed since last year. An email about this
requirement and the deadline of March 19th 2015 has been sent to each
individual driver maintainer, as well as the mailing list [1]. This
driver is being removed because the maintainer does not have a CI
reporting to ensure their driver integration is successful. Therfore, we
can not validate the driver is working in Cinder today in a continuous
way.

DocImpact
[1]- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-January/054614.html

Change-Id: Idd348bb81680c3f06a3a732d7e2ae657cceaa6f2

commit_message:
Allow to configure update available resource interval

Periodic task interval of update available resource now is always
60 seconds (default value). Under some circumstances, Nova driver
may require a long time frame to sync with hypervisor. So it will
be useful to allow this value to be configured instead of static.

DocImpact
Closes-Bug: 1391029

Change-Id: I30c087fb693aff9bfe7844250af5fd1e8dad647e

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-19 15:20:02.000000000', 'files': ['nailgun/nailgun/task/helpers.py', 'nailgun/nailgun/test/unit/test_task_helpers.py', 'nailgun/nailgun/test/integration/test_task_managers.py'], 'message': 'Fix error with no updating of action log after empty cluster deletion

In case user deletes empty cluster through api, action log is not updated
for cluster_deletion task as orm related error occurs in updating routine.
The reason for it is that we try to operate on task instance which
corresponding row was removed from db and hence attempt to access
attributes, marked on model as deffered, produces mentioned error.

This patch wraps getting of task.cache attribute into separate
try..except block in which case we only lose update for "output" section
of additional_info for action_log entry.

Unit test for implemented task helper routine, modeling situation with
referring to "deffered" attribute of instance, which corresponding db row
was deleted, added.

Integration test that emulates user's action leading to the bug added.

Change-Id: Id296c403423e314dd88063883141aff661c7aa9e
Closes-Bug: #1407716
'}]
commit_message:
Fix error with no updating of action log after empty cluster deletion

In case user deletes empty cluster through api, action log is not updated
for cluster_deletion task as orm related error occurs in updating routine.
The reason for it is that we try to operate on task instance which
corresponding row was removed from db and hence attempt to access
attributes, marked on model as deffered, produces mentioned error.

This patch wraps getting of task.cache attribute into separate
try..except block in which case we only lose update for "output" section
of additional_info for action_log entry.

Unit test for implemented task helper routine, modeling situation with
referring to "deffered" attribute of instance, which corresponding db row
was deleted, added.

Integration test that emulates user's action leading to the bug added.

Change-Id: Id296c403423e314dd88063883141aff661c7aa9e
Closes-Bug: #1407716

commit_message:
Fix common misspellings

Wikipedia's list of common misspellings [1] has a machine-readable
version.  This patch fixes those misspellings mentioned in the list
which don't have multiple right variants (as e.g. "accension", which can
be both "accession" and "ascension"), such misspellings are left
untouched.  The list of changes was manually re-checked for false
positives.

[1] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Lists_of_common_misspellings/For_machines

Change-Id: Ib9b61347ba94ee09954841a342cbbbb44da9d8fe
Signed-off-by: Martin Kletzander <mkletzan@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Add logging for an image registration

An image registration by s3 manifest is performed in a separate thread.
So occured errors are not reported to user.
Original Nova EC2 code contains error logging for such thread. Now we've
copied it.

subject: Remove get_admin_context function
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-03-20 22:21:16.000000000', 'files': ['ec2api/api/image.py', 'ec2api/tests/unit/test_middleware.py', 'ec2api/context.py'], 'message': "Remove get_admin_context function

Originally (in Nova) this function was intendend to get context to get
full access to DB, i.e. to read previously deleted data (with deleted
field is on) or across tenant data access.
Since ec2api database has no ability to hide data instead of delete it,
and API requests for other tenant data are managed by special DB API
methods, we don't need such context elevation.

Change-Id: I16ce6f973872a320858d27d87ed8928958169b3f
"}]
commit_message:
Remove get_admin_context function

Originally (in Nova) this function was intendend to get context to get
full access to DB, i.e. to read previously deleted data (with deleted
field is on) or across tenant data access.
Since ec2api database has no ability to hide data instead of delete it,
and API requests for other tenant data are managed by special DB API
methods, we don't need such context elevation.

Change-Id: I16ce6f973872a320858d27d87ed8928958169b3f

commit_message:
Renames for consistent namespaces

Castellan was using both key_mgr and keymgr for module names, leading to
inconsistent namespaces such as:

castellan.keymgr.key_mgr.KeyManager

This CR renames both instances to key_manager to be consistent with the
program name.

Change-Id: Ie07a70c14939b6c797e812c441d29218c2940ade

commit_message:
Reorganize hierarchy of exception classes

Separate ancestors of ec2api internal and aws compliant exceptions.
EC2APIException - base exception class for ec2api with formatting
support
EC2MetadataException - still covers internal exception of ec2api
metadata service
EC2Exception - still covers AWS compliant exceptions
EC2xxxException - derive EC2Exception and are intended to group
exceptions by kind

Also remove unused attributes and code from base exception class.
Fix string constant style to be 'xxx' wherever it's possible.

Change-Id: I398c1e8e1816e0d4073fa5d3fdf0c0a939470399

commit_message:
Get rid of Nova DB access

Important features:
- Nova client with microversion support is required.
- Nova API server may not support microversion 2.3 (not tested).
- Attaching volumes are not displayed in an instance bdm. Because Cinder
volume doesn't yet contain attachment info (which contains a device
name), and Nova instance volumes_attached doesn't contain a device name
(mountpoint). But a bdm must contain it.

Other features:
- v2.3 is requested always
- RunInstance result is formatted w/o extra v2.3 info, so it doesn't
contain rootDeviceName and other such info
- if rootDeviceName property is empty it's omitted instead of
to report fake /dev/sda1 as Nova EC2 does it. This leads to omit
rootDeviceType property in this case as well.
Also the same is done for corresponding image's properties.
- deleteOnTermination volume property is omitted for volume at all, and
for instance bdm if Nova doesn't report it. Previously this volume
property contained 'False' only.
- DescribeVolumes isn't used in DescribeInstances (as opposed to
DescribeNetworkInterfaces), because both methods require actual state
of corresponding OS objects, so we prevent duplication of OS requests.
- Not merged Nova client is used
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/152569/

Also:
- fix multi-run instances for EC2 Classic mode
- safe getting of OS instance security groups
- ec2context module alias is renamed to ec2_context, as it is in other
code
- fakes.CinderVolume is renamed to local standard OSVolume
- fakes.OSInstance it transformed to be initialized from a dictionary,
as it is for other fakes.OSXxx objects
- fix code style

Depends-On: Icf2b9739aaf87b4c9af13ad64a310081a68f776e
Change-Id: Id65ea0f56ffd889286d5ca082e1daf2643205c52

commit_message:
Removing the debian folder

On Debian systems, we require upstream to *not* want upstream
to add a debian folder on their upstream code. This goes against
all the worflows we have for maintaining packages inside a specific
branch which contains that debian folder.

As I am about to package Barbican in Debian (reminder: I'm the
package maintainer for everything else in OpenStack in Debian), I
need this folder to go away, so I can do my packaging work. I
certainly appreciate to have a template package to start with though,
so thanks to whoever wrote that (it will appear in debian/copyright).

Change-Id: I1adadb4b95345308f613f3a52b9fffdbc9229bee

commit_message:
Fix logging mistake in swift backup driver

After recent swift driver refactoring a small mistake was introduced
causing c-bak to log an exception because of wrong number of arguments
to format a string. This commit fixes the issue.

Change-Id: I2e322ae6a2495771c89fa25ab5474da20eecc80d
Closes-Bug: 1434188

commit_message:
Remove downgrade from existing migrations

Create a test that verifies that no migration has a downgrade.

Related cross-project spec: https://review.openstack.org/152337

commit_message:
Removing Zadara driver for no reported CI

CI deadlines were set and pushed since last year. An email about this
requirement and the deadline of March 19th 2015 has been sent to each
individual driver maintainer, as well as the mailing list [1]. This
driver is being removed because the maintainer does not have a CI
reporting to ensure their driver integration is successful. Therfore, we
can not validate the driver is working in Cinder today in a continuous
way.

DocImpact
[1]-
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-January/054614.html

Change-Id: I016e22c857f520a7eb79e1ed5b36735a97f68b68

subject: Use unique refs for RSA container example
revisions:

In a real world use of Barbican the secret refs in an RSA container
will all be different.  This CR changes the example that shows every
ref to be the same in favor of different refs to avoid confusion.

Change-Id: I6cd5c4202eb5623262cbf1485ea8a55680f37bed'}]
commit_message:
Use unique refs for RSA container example

In a real world use of Barbican the secret refs in an RSA container
will all be different.  This CR changes the example that shows every
ref to be the same in favor of different refs to avoid confusion.

Change-Id: I6cd5c4202eb5623262cbf1485ea8a55680f37bed

commit_message:
[Launch Instance Fix] Move instance name form to its own step

This moves the instance name/project selection off to its own step.

The instance count also moves there, but it probably should be on
the source step.

... though I cannot figure out why the graph includes the source
allocation count, since that's always 1 ...

Change-Id: I4a2f604d49fdb37629d7b89233222b13a4fb2999
Closes-Bug: 1435648

commit_message:
Drop support for SQL Schema Downgrades

Remove downgrade from the --autogenerate option of neutron-db-manage.
Add tests to check that downgrade options cannot be used.

Related cross-project spec: https://review.openstack.org/152337
Partial-Bug: 1434103

Change-Id: Id2f7f521644828ab7fbc027c6037f76f0337e121

commit_message:
Removing Netapp FC drivers for no reported CI

CI deadlines were set and pushed since last year. An email about this
requirement and the deadline of March 19th 2015 has been sent to each
individual driver maintainer, as well as the mailing list [1]. This
driver is being removed because the maintainer does not have a CI
reporting to ensure their driver integration is successful. Therfore, we
can not validate the driver is working in Cinder today in a continuous
way.

DocImpact
[1]- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-January/054614.html

Change-Id: I85ed137ddb1929509f9930cd1de91671dde3db42

Shares with transitional states like 'creating' or 'deleting' should not be
allowed to be unmanaged.
For the moment "manage/unmanage" operation is allowed only for driver mode

on top of share servers should be restricted on API level.

Closes-Bug: #1434642
Closes-Bug: #1434511
'}]
commit_message:
Add share state verification for API 'unmanage'

Shares with transitional states like 'creating' or 'deleting' should not be
allowed to be unmanaged.
For the moment "manage/unmanage" operation is allowed only for driver mode
without handling of share servers. So, API operations against shares created
on top of share servers should be restricted on API level.

Change-Id: I73b554448eadcb96ef00f44535014e14dea91472
Closes-Bug: #1434642
Closes-Bug: #1434511

commit_message:
TOSCA: Add missing artifacts references

The TOSCA wordpress template is missing artifacts. These artifacts were tested
with actual deployment but never added here. Unit tests are there for this
template for TOSCA parser side and we are working on to create tests for the
full translated template with HOT mapping.

commit_message:
Removing DRBD driver for no reported CI

CI deadlines were set and pushed since last year. An email about this
requirement and the deadline of March 19th 2015 has been sent to each
individual driver maintainer, as well as the mailing list [1]. This
driver is being removed because the maintainer does not have a CI
reporting to ensure their driver integration is successful. Therfore, we
can not validate the driver is working in Cinder today in a continuous
way.

DocImpact
[1]- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-January/054614.html

Change-Id: If4b119ec6ca80dcf28530e77e1f98bda04ba6eab

commit_message:
pip_mirror param for test image boot config

This allows a local pip mirror to be used to install the heat
agent tools (such as the mirror built by devstack when
HEAT_BUILD_PIP_MIRROR=True).

Change-Id: Ib48d652fba8dabe1e94203d44278b2bae56b356c

commit_message:
Fix the inconsistent info of availability zone

If the default availability zone is replaced with the
newly-created one, then it causes the info of availability
zone to be inconsistent for every retrieval in the process
of launching new VM instance.

This bug fix will not work if the availability zone is not
specified (e.g. via CLI of nova boot).

Change-Id: Id3f3fab0d87f5bb3b9038681b355db84d22a29a7
Closes-Bug: #1390033

commit_message:
Removing Nexenta driver for no reported CI

CI deadlines were set and pushed since last year. An email about this
requirement and the deadline of March 19th 2015 has been sent to each
individual driver maintainer, as well as the mailing list [1]. This
driver is being removed because the maintainer does not have a CI
reporting to ensure their driver integration is successful. Therfore, we
can not validate the driver is working in Cinder today in a continuous
way.

DocImpact
[1]- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-January/054614.html

Change-Id: I732612e671c57c0b611f1016f22c89a886a317f7

commit_message:
Fix common misspellings

Wikipedia's list of common misspellings [1] has a machine-readable
version.  This patch fixes those misspellings mentioned in the list
which don't have multiple right variants (as e.g. "accension", which can
be both "accession" and "ascension"), such misspellings are left
untouched.  The list of changes was manually re-checked for false
positives.

[1] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Lists_of_common_misspellings/For_machines

Change-Id: Iea72412c82ac9ec8bf09bb80057e073bf8f672f6
Signed-off-by: Martin Kletzander <mkletzan@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Fix naming convention in configuration.rst

According to OpenStack naming conventions [1], we should use
keystone instead of Keystone.

There are several occurrences throughout the code and docs,
fixing the main configuration doc first.

[1] https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Conventions

Change-Id: I51beb8397bb3bec07a367fbcf57d9e2b756a2137

commit_message:
Removing StorPool driver for no reported CI

CI deadlines were set and pushed since last year. An email about this
requirement and the deadline of March 19th 2015 has been sent to each
individual driver maintainer, as well as the mailing list [1]. This
driver is being removed because the maintainer does not have a CI
reporting to ensure their driver integration is successful. Therfore, we
can not validate the driver is working in Cinder today in a continuous
way.

DocImpact
[1]- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-January/054614.html

commit_message:
Fix metering agent failure when chain missing

The metering agent will fail if one of the iptables chains
is missing, which will cause errors extracting data from
all the other chains. Add a simple try/except to let the
loop continue.

Closes-Bug: #1421037

Change-Id: I370ee0e2cc58ca7e1c5ef9bf4dbcce5abf7545a1

subject: Deal with PEP-0476 certificate chaining checking
revisions:
[{'number': 6, 'created': '2015-03-20 19:56:43.000000000', 'files': ['keystone/tests/unit/test_ssl.py'], 'message': 'Deal with PEP-0476 certificate chaining checking

PEP-0476 introduced more thorough certificate chain verification
for HTTPS connectivity; this was introduced in Python 2.7.9, and
breaks a number of unit tests in the keystone codebase.

Disable certificate chain verification for keystone SSL tests
using the backwards compatible SSLContext provided for this
purpose.

Change-Id: I6b5e975ed4c9abf3571212ba0e172eb653bb9281
Closes-Bug: #1403068
'}]
commit_message:
Deal with PEP-0476 certificate chaining checking

PEP-0476 introduced more thorough certificate chain verification
for HTTPS connectivity; this was introduced in Python 2.7.9, and
breaks a number of unit tests in the keystone codebase.

Disable certificate chain verification for keystone SSL tests
using the backwards compatible SSLContext provided for this
purpose.

Change-Id: I6b5e975ed4c9abf3571212ba0e172eb653bb9281
Closes-Bug: #1403068

commit_message:
make credential policy check ownership of credential

Currently, policy.json and policy.v3cloudsample.json only check if
the user from token matchs the user from url. However, we should
also check if the user owns the credential.

Change-Id: I5c8bbb6736b028d6cb693d2a35e018f28caeaa57
Closes-Bug: #1417366
Closes-Bug: #1417522

commit_message:
Implements stack lifecycle scheduler hints

This is a mechanism whereby when heat processes
a stack VM resource, the stack id, root stack id,
stack resource id, stack resource name and the
path in the stack (as a list of tuples,
(stackresourcename, stackname)) can be passed to
nova by heat as scheduler hints, to the
configured schedulers for nova.

Implements: blueprint stack-lifecycle-scheduler-hint
Co-Authored-By: Karolyn Chambers <chamberk@us.ibm.com>

Change-Id: I3e006339a41c469451bc3ee740018b285d3e0a65

commit_message:
Removing ZFSSA driver for no reported CI

CI deadlines were set and pushed since last year. An email about this
requirement and the deadline of March 19th 2015 has been sent to each
individual driver maintainer, as well as the mailing list [1]. This
driver is being removed because the maintainer does not have a CI
reporting to ensure their driver integration is successful. Therfore, we
can not validate the driver is working in Cinder today in a continuous
way.

DocImpact
[1]- http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-January/054614.html
Change-Id: I5126ee5c56d2a7382e67626d28197eafa5940be5

commit_message:
Logging not using oslo.i18n guidelines

Part of multi-patch set for easier chunks.

There have been quite a few instances found where the
i18n guidelines are not being followed. I believe this
has helped lead to some of the confusion around how to
correctly do this. Other developers see this code and
assume it is an example of the correct usage.

This patch attempts to clean up most of those violations
in the existing codebase to hopefully help avoid some of
that confusion in reviews.

Some issues address:
* Correct log translation markers for different log levels
* Passing format values as arguments to call, not preformatting
* Not forcing translation via six.text_type and others

Guidelines can be found here:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.i18n/guidelines.html

Hacking checks will not be able to identify all violations of
the guidelines, but it could be useful for catching obvious ones
such as LOG.info("No markers!").

Change-Id: I38f52c6408b47ccb59ec2064b360f7d4427d6830
Partial-bug: 1433216

commit_message:
Update pod_delete call for new log message

The latest kubernetes has changed the log message when a pod
is not found, from "pod 'x' not found" to "pods 'x' not found".
To handle this, and maintain compatibility, this removes the
check for 'pod ' and just checks the log message for
"'x' not found".

Change-Id: Id3a847a576beed383bb0e382afa545828047648b
Closes-Bug: #1435575

subject: Ensure configdrive isn't mounted in CoreOS ramdisks
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-24 00:56:46.000000000', 'files': ['ironic/drivers/modules/agent_config.template', 'ironic/drivers/modules/pxe_config.template'], 'message': "Ensure configdrive isn't mounted in CoreOS ramdisks

Temporary workaround for bug #1433812. CoreOS processes the
cloud-config.yml too late the boot process to prevent mounting and
processing the configdrive. Pass coreos.configdrive=0 on the kernel
command line to ensure this doesn't occur, as it can be a security risk
(previous tenants may have written a malicious configdrive, and it would
be read before being cleaned).

Long-term, we should remove this workaround and either completely remove
the mount units from the ramdisk during the build process or get a
better fix from upstream (https://github.com/coreos/bugs/issues/314).

Change-Id: Ia8d05b6880bf1387b64aeec45ce1161e343e53a9
Partial-bug: 1433812
"}]
commit_message:
Ensure configdrive isn't mounted in CoreOS ramdisks

Temporary workaround for bug #1433812. CoreOS processes the
cloud-config.yml too late the boot process to prevent mounting and
processing the configdrive. Pass coreos.configdrive=0 on the kernel
command line to ensure this doesn't occur, as it can be a security risk
(previous tenants may have written a malicious configdrive, and it would
be read before being cleaned).

Long-term, we should remove this workaround and either completely remove
the mount units from the ramdisk during the build process or get a
better fix from upstream (https://github.com/coreos/bugs/issues/314).

Change-Id: Ia8d05b6880bf1387b64aeec45ce1161e343e53a9
Partial-bug: 1433812

commit_message:
Fix backporting objects with sub-objects that can look falsey

List objects can appear falsey if they have no elements. So, when we backport,
we need to explicitly check for Noneness instead of falsiness.

Change-Id: I8457889f9725c77efaa7ecbe03d62b7c593eeac4

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-19 16:33:58.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/tests/test_volume.py', 'cinder/volume/api.py'], 'message': 'Tests: Fix az test failure when PYTHONHASHSEED != 0

The test_list_availability_zones_enabled_service test calls
a method which returns a tuple that is generated from a dict.
This is compared to a tuple in the test, which can fail when
PYTHONHASHSEED is not 0, due to the tuples containing elements
in different orders.  (Because the dict used to build the tuple
was ordered differently.)

For this test, we can convert to lists and sort them to do the
comparison, since the ordering is not important.

Partial-Bug: #1348818

Change-Id: Ib7e5d59073e5e243450e28492d68942f6088bb5f
'}]
commit_message:
Tests: Fix az test failure when PYTHONHASHSEED != 0

The test_list_availability_zones_enabled_service test calls
a method which returns a tuple that is generated from a dict.
This is compared to a tuple in the test, which can fail when
PYTHONHASHSEED is not 0, due to the tuples containing elements
in different orders.  (Because the dict used to build the tuple
was ordered differently.)

For this test, we can convert to lists and sort them to do the
comparison, since the ordering is not important.

Partial-Bug: #1348818

Change-Id: Ib7e5d59073e5e243450e28492d68942f6088bb5f

commit_message:
[Launch Instance Fix] Launch instance refreshes instance tables

Added ability to specify a URL to redirect to upon success of the
launch instance wizard.  This is done through a configuration object
passed into the launch method.  The mechanism that opens the modal is
configured to respond to a positive result by relocating to the
configured success URL.

Change-Id: I622a42e34a94d04bc9b80432be3aaa6752a1c82e
Closes-Bug: 1434221

[{'number': 5, 'created': '2015-03-20 06:49:32.000000000', 'files': ['doc/source/command-objects/network.rst', 'openstackclient/network/v2/network.py', 'openstackclient/tests/identity/v2_0/fakes.py', 'openstackclient/tests/network/v2/test_network.py'], 'message': "Add project and domain params to network create

Without this patch, openstackclient has no way to specify to which
project a network belongs upon creation. Instead, it uses the project
ID that the user is authenticating with to fill the tenant_id column.
This is a problem because an admin user is unable to specify a project
for a non-admin network. To fix this and to improve feature parity with
the neutron client, this patch adds project and domain parameters to
the network create command and uses the given project name to look up
the project ID.

Neutron does not allow the project to be changed after creation, so no
such parameter has been added to the neutron set command.

Neutron calls the field 'tenant_id', but this change exposes the
parameter as '--project' to support the newer terminology.

If no project is specified, the client defaults to the previous
behavior of using the auth project.

Change-Id: Ia33ff7d599542c5b88baf2a69b063a23089a3cc4
"}]
commit_message:
Add project and domain params to network create

Without this patch, openstackclient has no way to specify to which
project a network belongs upon creation. Instead, it uses the project
ID that the user is authenticating with to fill the tenant_id column.
This is a problem because an admin user is unable to specify a project
for a non-admin network. To fix this and to improve feature parity with
the neutron client, this patch adds project and domain parameters to
the network create command and uses the given project name to look up
the project ID.

Neutron does not allow the project to be changed after creation, so no
such parameter has been added to the neutron set command.

Neutron calls the field 'tenant_id', but this change exposes the
parameter as '--project' to support the newer terminology.

If no project is specified, the client defaults to the previous
behavior of using the auth project.

Change-Id: Ia33ff7d599542c5b88baf2a69b063a23089a3cc4

commit_message:
Update some ResizeClaimTestCase tests

The resource tracker is being converted to use objects. This patch
removes some tests from ResizeClaimTestCase in test_resource_tracker.py
and adds equivalent tests to test_tracker.py. By doing it this way, it
can be seen that the old and new tests both pass in the gate before the
resource tracker is converted to use migration objects.

Partially implements blueprint make-resource-tracker-use-objects

Change-Id: I464e1180b5c3e0d876d40318df334b4e07005a42

commit_message:
Don't run neutron-large-ops on neutron advanced services

The neutron-large-ops test doesn't exercise any advanced services so
don't run it on openstack/neutron-* repo changes. Remove
neutron-large-ops from integrated-gate-neutron and add it to
openstack/neutron.

It will still get run on projects that use large-ops

Change-Id: I2c08e0b1c8730a02692c9a286fae321ed58e5a98

commit_message:
Merge heat-kubernetes pull request 14

Pull request 14 changes the start order of Kubernetes.  The master
now starts first, and the minion starts after the master completes.

This prevents flanneld in the minions from timing out and failing to
start the kubernetes services on the minions.

See:
https://github.com/larsks/heat-kubernetes/pull/14/

Change-Id: Ia823fd3593dc7c5d9d9c6327e009b833ad586a5c
Closes-bug: #1434468

commit_message:
Add native OVSDB implementation of OVSDB API

This patch adds a native OVSDB protocol version of the new OVSDB
API. As such, it does not require using sudo/rootwrap but instead
uses the OVS IDL Python library that ships with openvswitch.

Doc-Impact
Implements: blueprint vsctl-to-ovsdb
Change-Id: I2bf5ba7f4607cec324ea841f0fea7bad274faffc

commit_message:
Fix common misspellings

Wikipedia's list of common misspellings [1] has a machine-readable
version.  This patch fixes those misspellings mentioned in the list
which don't have multiple right variants (as e.g. "accension", which can
be both "accession" and "ascension"), such misspellings are left
untouched.  The list of changes was manually re-checked for false
positives.

[1] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Lists_of_common_misspellings/For_machines

Change-Id: Ic53e9a848280d50e69306abc98194890ac298ff2
Signed-off-by: Martin Kletzander <mkletzan@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Add support for Oracle Linux 7 and later.

Most of the changes revolves around using MySQL rather than MariaDB,
plus enabling the addon repos on public-yum.oracle.com.
The patch just touch the areas where there is a divergence between the
Fedora and Oracle distributions and in all other cases the is_fedora
will result in the correct decision to be made and left as is.

Collapsed the is_suse and is_oraclelinux into a single check in
configure_database_mysql and cleanup_database_mysql

Added Oracle Linux to MAINTAINERS.rst

Rather than duplicating most of the Redhat version check code, added
a check in the block to do the determination if it is Oracle Linux

Change-Id: I5f1f15106329eec67aa008b17847fa44863f243f

commit_message:
zuul: add check-grenade-dsvm-neutron to tempest checks

Since check-grenade-dsvm-neutron is part of Neutron checks, we should
add this job to Tempest too because Javelin could break Grenade/Neutron
jobs.
A recent failure in Neutron gate was not detected, with this job we
would have been able to detect the issue and the patch would not have
been merged in Tempest.

Change-Id: Ic095fd1f42acb3748a7b7bf61d188155060d0d61

We are rapidly progressing to the point where we need to have a
federation and kerberos and possibly other authentication mechanisms for
Django Openstack Auth.

With this change we can reuse Django's inbuilt multiple authentication
backends while sharing the common logic of fetching an unscoped token,
listing projects and rescoping it.

This will allow us to maintain new mechanisms out of tree with the

Change-Id: Icbdb339b1b7d8776c03c8ac1c57506d8309810a1
"}]
commit_message:
Extract a reusable authentication base from DOA

We are rapidly progressing to the point where we need to have a
federation and kerberos and possibly other authentication mechanisms for
Django Openstack Auth.

With this change we can reuse Django's inbuilt multiple authentication
backends while sharing the common logic of fetching an unscoped token,
listing projects and rescoping it.

This will allow us to maintain new mechanisms out of tree with the
correct dependencies set up.

Change-Id: Icbdb339b1b7d8776c03c8ac1c57506d8309810a1

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-03-23 16:12:38.000000000', 'files': ['utils/jenkins/fuel_syntax_check.sh', 'utils/jenkins/fuel_unit_tests.sh'], 'message': "Don't run syntax/unit tests for removed modules

We're running syntax and unit tests for changed modules only.

But for removed modules, we fail to 'pushd $mod' and thus run test
functions inside current working directory, which is not correct.

We should test if changed module dir exists before trying to run
tests for it.

Fuel-CI: disable

Change-Id: If1ab6850943b7aed7a48479625d8daa0243594f6
Closes-bug: #1435401
"}]
commit_message:
Don't run syntax/unit tests for removed modules

We're running syntax and unit tests for changed modules only.

But for removed modules, we fail to 'pushd $mod' and thus run test
functions inside current working directory, which is not correct.

We should test if changed module dir exists before trying to run
tests for it.

Fuel-CI: disable

Change-Id: If1ab6850943b7aed7a48479625d8daa0243594f6
Closes-bug: #1435401

commit_message:
Fix udev NIC renaming issue

To prevent accidental NIC renaming we need to create empty udev rule
named /etc/udev/rules.d/75-persistent-net-generator.rules to disable
adding of any entries into /etc/udev/rules.d/70-persistent-net.rules

Change-Id: Idf2dc7a02ce4093fabbc7a518443aa9eacfc141d
Closes-Bug: #1422826

commit_message:
Fixes the rabbitmq user which defaults to guest

This changes the user to admin/mypass which is in line with the other
accounts. Guest gets removed from the rabbit run and if you have
multiple machines attempting you can only locally connect via guest.

http://www.rabbitmq.com/access-control.html

Change-Id: I5694aeca7007280e93fc1fd8f9c9595e21ab9d9e

commit_message:
Add identity v3 jobs to periodic-qa

Identity v3 jobs are only running as experimental right now.
Those jobs use the auth_version=v3 setting in tempest, so that
all tokens are obtained via the identity v3 api.

Adding them to periodic QA to make verify if any regression is
introduced, until we start using v3 in check and or gate.

Change-Id: Ic78b4626c90951deb27fd4f0bd0558b75aa6b5b2
Partially-implements: bp/keystone-v3-jobs

commit_message:
Use zuul-cloner in project-requirements-change

This will use the typcial Zuul branch fallback logic.  The current
branch parameter to this script is ZUUL_BRANCH, so the logic is
equivalent.

Also, adjust the test for include_dev so that dev versions are
permitted for master and feature branches.

subject: Remove httpretty from resource tests
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-03-18 17:38:18.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/tests/test_resource.py'], 'message': 'Remove httpretty from resource tests

The major change here is that httpretty is removed from test_resource in
favor of using a Mock session based off of the Session class.

Common replacements were:
* stub_url usage was replaced with a Mock return_value on the verb that
  was being stubbed.
* Places where we were accessing httpretty.last_request use some form of
  call_args on session verbs. Additionally, for the common case of
  checking whether an expected URL was generated to be called,
  assertCalledURL was created on the ResourceTests class.
* Some minor rearrangements to move several test methods out of TestFind
  and back into ResourceTests where they belong.

Change-Id: I743dc31965b7f2329f5d5ad80fea09e0da0cba73
'}]
commit_message:
Remove httpretty from resource tests

The major change here is that httpretty is removed from test_resource in
favor of using a Mock session based off of the Session class.

Common replacements were:
* stub_url usage was replaced with a Mock return_value on the verb that
  was being stubbed.
* Places where we were accessing httpretty.last_request use some form of
  call_args on session verbs. Additionally, for the common case of
  checking whether an expected URL was generated to be called,
  assertCalledURL was created on the ResourceTests class.
* Some minor rearrangements to move several test methods out of TestFind
  and back into ResourceTests where they belong.

Change-Id: I743dc31965b7f2329f5d5ad80fea09e0da0cba73

commit_message:
Disable oslo_messaging debug logging

We previously set the default log level for oslo.messaging to INFO, when
we switched over to oslo_messaging this didn't get changed.

This should significantly reduce the amount of logging, in one tempest
run, nova-compute logs 13k oslo_messaging debug logs.

Change-Id: I560c679af420f1da8054f163f80ae1e39bb7d089

commit_message:
Fallback to master on requirements check job

If the change having its requirements checked is on a branch that global
requirements does not have fallback to checking against global
requirements master. This will handle feature branches not being on
global requirements for projects that have feature branches and need to
update requirements.

Change-Id: Id930cc14805fabe46321ea4262a2271bce5b04ee

subject: Fix test_netutils: stop patches
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-23 13:50:56.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_utils/tests/test_netutils.py'], 'message': "Fix test_netutils: stop patches

test_netutils monkey patches os.path.exists() and
six.moves.builtins.open() using mock, but it didn't stop the patchs.

A side effect is that test_excutils started to fail when executed after
test_netutils. Randomly, test_excutils was executed before or after
test_netutils, so test_excutils failure was random.

Closes-Bug: #1433800
Change-Id: Ifbe79c52f34b4373721e9aa2e22eb86f39b60b87
"}]
commit_message:
Fix test_netutils: stop patches

test_netutils monkey patches os.path.exists() and
six.moves.builtins.open() using mock, but it didn't stop the patchs.

A side effect is that test_excutils started to fail when executed after
test_netutils. Randomly, test_excutils was executed before or after
test_netutils, so test_excutils failure was random.

Closes-Bug: #1433800
Change-Id: Ifbe79c52f34b4373721e9aa2e22eb86f39b60b87

commit_message:
openflow app: Remove mistakenly added keys to subnets in sync_port

We already hold the mac->port_data connection in
(unsurprisingly) TenantTopo.mac_to_port_data.

Further more TenantTopo.subnets is indexed by subnet.id not the mac
address.

Change-Id: I7dae92d70c4c7493bce0f09a176eb369ae6a9979
Signed-off-by: Saggi Mizrahi <saggi.mizrahi@huawei.com>

variable provided by the SAML assertion (or claim in the case of OpenID
Connect). Logic would dictate that the 'remote_id_attribute' value is
searched for against the 'remote_id' field in the backend where identity
providers are stored. Instead, we are doing the lookup against the 'id'
field.

This patch makes the websso code look the identity provider up by the
remote ID.

Change-Id: I1dc666782929902a3a4f478baef2b729757b0dc5
Closes-Bug: 1434701
"}]
commit_message:
Lookup identity provider by remote_id for websso

When using the websso feature in keystone, the identity provider is
looked up based on the value of the 'remote_id_attribute' environment
variable provided by the SAML assertion (or claim in the case of OpenID
Connect). Logic would dictate that the 'remote_id_attribute' value is
searched for against the 'remote_id' field in the backend where identity
providers are stored. Instead, we are doing the lookup against the 'id'
field.

This patch makes the websso code look the identity provider up by the
remote ID.

Change-Id: I1dc666782929902a3a4f478baef2b729757b0dc5
Closes-Bug: 1434701

When revert-resize call is finished, it doesn't clear instance
files from destination node for non-shared instance storage.

The driver call, which is responsible for destroying destination

both source and destination host shares the same instance storage.

The check_instance_shared_storage rpc-call had no host information,
hence the manager call for check_instance_shared_storage was checking
instance storage on destination host itself and returning True even
if it is non-shared storage.

commit_message:
Delete instance files from dest host in revert-resize

When revert-resize call is finished, it doesn't clear instance
files from destination node for non-shared instance storage.

The driver call, which is responsible for destroying destination
host instance is not deleting instance files, because it finds that
both source and destination host shares the same instance storage.

The check_instance_shared_storage rpc-call had no host information,
hence the manager call for check_instance_shared_storage was checking
instance storage on destination host itself and returning True even
if it is non-shared storage.

Added host parameter to check_instance_shared_storage rpc-call,
so that in manager call check_instance_shared_storage method get
executed on source compute node and returns True/False based on
shared/non-shared storage.

Closes-Bug: #1418855
Change-Id: Ic529b1c2c1cfd914facb14941e4bb641db6a0e82

subject: Fix issue with stdout not appearing on console for converge
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-03-18 17:06:05.000000000', 'files': ['Rakefile'], 'message': 'Fix issue with stdout not appearing on console for converge

Depending upon how the chef-client is envoked, it does a
STDOUT.tty? check to determine if output should be sent to
the doc formatter as STDOUT.  In many cases this check returns
false.  To override this, I added the --force-formatter option
to the chef-client so we can always get the output to STDOUT.
This will help with allowing batch testing to capture
all output in log files for a testing suite run.

Change-Id: Ibde012f9c3aa281ff1477c9b7e1d1ffa415e97cd
'}]
commit_message:
Fix issue with stdout not appearing on console for converge

Depending upon how the chef-client is envoked, it does a
STDOUT.tty? check to determine if output should be sent to
the doc formatter as STDOUT.  In many cases this check returns
false.  To override this, I added the --force-formatter option
to the chef-client so we can always get the output to STDOUT.
This will help with allowing batch testing to capture
all output in log files for a testing suite run.

Change-Id: Ibde012f9c3aa281ff1477c9b7e1d1ffa415e97cd

commit_message:
Move testresources/testscenarios into test-requirements

Commit 6ccea346d9609d47b188b33c686f49ce3f4f9b14 moved testscenarios out
of test-requirements and into requirements.txt (and added testresources)
because the oslo_db.sqlalchemy.provision module now imports
testresources.

Refactored code that used testresources and testscenarios to live under
tests directory

This is particularly important for distro packagers that don't really
want to package and ship testresources/scenarios for test code that they
may or may not be packaging.

Co-Authored-By: Matt Riedemann <mriedem@us.ibm.com> 
Closes-Bug: #1429233
Change-Id: I6f378a41311ba2cd710f96eb36305be3d9073baa

commit_message:
fix path matching redux

This adjusts patch matching to require that our matched string starts
at a '/' boundary, this makes it so that we don't accidentally match
test names in log file names.

Tests are adjusted to support this new restriction.

Change-Id: I93908e119f6787eeda29107faf9a71f29f7d6f50

commit_message:
Remove strutils from oslo-incubator

This change goes along with the work to get away from
oslo-incubator modules to using the new oslo libraries.
The strutils module moved to the oslo_utils library and
should no longer be used from oslo-incubator.

Additionally, merging this change removes a dependency on
gettextutils, allowing us to remove another deprecated
module.

Change-Id: Ibd4e848b526c67cad660c31038df718ac416c6e1

subject: Make nova-compute-network use a data volume container
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2015-03-22 15:55:29.000000000', 'files': ['docker/nova-compute/nova-libvirt/Dockerfile', 'docker/nova-compute/nova-network/Dockerfile', 'docker/nova-compute/nova-compute-data/build', 'docker/nova-compute/nova-compute-data/Dockerfile', 'docker/nova-compute/nova-compute/Dockerfile', 'compose/nova-compute-network.yml'], 'message': "Make nova-compute-network use a data volume container

A data volume container is far superior to bind mounting the
host's shared directories.  It preserves the idempotency,
immutability and declarative properties of the containers.

The way this works in practice is that a data volume container is
created.  Then when the containers start they use LVM to access
the filesystem where /var/lib/docker is contained.  Then the
container startup logic bindmounts the data volume stored on the
host filesystem in /var/lib/docker/vfs/dir/ID.  This prevents
people with access to the host operating system from damaging
the contents of the data container.

It does mean that now we must use tools/stop to stop our containers
rather than tools/cleanup-containers -f.

This is a containers best practice.  For more details see:

https://docs.docker.com/userguide/dockervolumes/

Big credit goes to Danyeon Hansen for seeding this idea in the
mariadb containers.

Note occasionally docker-compose start/stop seems to not want to stop
a container.  This bug needs to be addressed upstream separately
from our utilization of this best practice.

Change-Id: Iaa1419f606e1b1b7a7560a095c49e79d643164f1
"}]
commit_message:
Make nova-compute-network use a data volume container

A data volume container is far superior to bind mounting the
host's shared directories.  It preserves the idempotency,
immutability and declarative properties of the containers.

The way this works in practice is that a data volume container is
created.  Then when the containers start they use LVM to access
the filesystem where /var/lib/docker is contained.  Then the
container startup logic bindmounts the data volume stored on the
host filesystem in /var/lib/docker/vfs/dir/ID.  This prevents
people with access to the host operating system from damaging
the contents of the data container.

It does mean that now we must use tools/stop to stop our containers
rather than tools/cleanup-containers -f.

This is a containers best practice.  For more details see:

https://docs.docker.com/userguide/dockervolumes/

Big credit goes to Danyeon Hansen for seeding this idea in the
mariadb containers.

Note occasionally docker-compose start/stop seems to not want to stop
a container.  This bug needs to be addressed upstream separately
from our utilization of this best practice.

Change-Id: Iaa1419f606e1b1b7a7560a095c49e79d643164f1

[Launch Instance Fix] Filter AKI and ARI Images

AKI and ARI image types should be filtered from the
list of available images. They are not directly launchable.

In addition, only images with status of active should be shown.

Closes-Bug: #1434287

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-03-23 18:20:40.000000000', 'files': ['nova_powervm/virt/powervm/driver.py', 'nova_powervm/virt/powervm/tasks/storage.py', 'nova_powervm/tests/virt/powervm/test_driver.py', 'nova_powervm/virt/powervm/media.py', 'nova_powervm/tests/virt/powervm/data/fake_vios_feed_no_vg.txt', 'nova_powervm/tests/virt/powervm/test_media.py'], 'message': 'Migrate media to support multi VIOS

The media.py file is used to attach the config drive to the VM via a
virtual optical media.  Initially, the code required a single static
Virtual I/O Server that it could connect to.

However, PowerVM systems support multiple Virtual I/O Servers.  In case
one is offline, the code should simply move over to the other Virtual
I/O Server (if there is one or more available).

This change supports this scenario.  Changes because of this:
 - Removed the need for the vio_map to be passed into the media.py
 - Used static variables to significantly reduce the overhead of
   validation.
 - Consolidated the CreateCfgDrive and ConnectCfgDrive tasks into a
   single method.  This was required to maintain VIO precision upon the
   scsi mapping.

Change-Id: I39abf747b3437be15ce927b71eb9f1e53599609e
'}]
commit_message:
Migrate media to support multi VIOS

The media.py file is used to attach the config drive to the VM via a
virtual optical media.  Initially, the code required a single static
Virtual I/O Server that it could connect to.

However, PowerVM systems support multiple Virtual I/O Servers.  In case
one is offline, the code should simply move over to the other Virtual
I/O Server (if there is one or more available).

This change supports this scenario.  Changes because of this:
 - Removed the need for the vio_map to be passed into the media.py
 - Used static variables to significantly reduce the overhead of
   validation.
 - Consolidated the CreateCfgDrive and ConnectCfgDrive tasks into a
   single method.  This was required to maintain VIO precision upon the
   scsi mapping.

Change-Id: I39abf747b3437be15ce927b71eb9f1e53599609e

Use pypowervm LPARBuilder

LPARBuilder.

commit_message:
Fix unstack.sh to stop stop_dstat when it is disabled.

unstack.sh always stop dstat process, however unstack.sh show 'dstat: no process
found' when dstat is disabled.
This patch stop function of stop_dstat, when dstat is disabled.

Change-Id: If9054826bed8a7fedd4f77ef4efef2c0ccd7f16e

commit_message:
Allow using shallow copy instead of deep copy

Certain projects (cinder at the least) seems to be
storing items that can not be deep copied without
issues; so to make it so that we can easily support
having this backend be the default backend always
used we need to be able to support a shallow copy
for when it is needed.

Change-Id: I16215b44870cef9ea60d144ba710c5d730e8b284

commit_message:
Fix common misspellings

Wikipedia's list of common misspellings [1] has a machine-readable
version.  This patch fixes those misspellings mentioned in the list
which don't have multiple right variants (as e.g. "accension", which can
be both "accession" and "ascension"), such misspellings are left
untouched.  The list of changes was manually re-checked for false
positives.

[1] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Lists_of_common_misspellings/For_machines

Change-Id: I9029d207b9e8f356fe71c3f20a74011c4d143bb5
Signed-off-by: Martin Kletzander <mkletzan@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Ilo drivers sets capabilities:boot_mode in node

Ilo drivers sets capabilities:boot_mode in node properties
if there is none.
For a node capable of booting in both bios and uefi, setting
of this property by driver prevents it from getting selected for
future deploys requests for other boot mode.
It would be selected only for deploy requests where flavor
extra_specs specifies capabilities:boot_mode with a value
matching with one set by driver in the node properties.

Closes-Bug: 1418327

Change-Id: I90571487840c6a74699a8fbfbac8035c3efb5672

If the registered callback was freed by the GC the proxy object would

commit_message:
Catch cases where callback was freed.

If the registered callback was freed by the GC the proxy object would
throw a reference which would get reported.
This is problematic as the user doesn't expect that.

Further more, we can't can't catch ReferenceError and ignore since the
underlying callback might throw that and there is no way to
differentiate with a proxy object.

By using a weakref.ref() object we have a concrete stage were we get the
strong reference and can clear the entry in case the callback was freed.

Change-Id: I2fad9a5b37f6975d4f017d822ab3233d9a6f22f6
Closes-Bug: #1432522
Signed-off-by: Saggi Mizrahi <saggi.mizrahi@huawei.com>

commit_message:
Fix regex for detecting milestone / build number

Modify regex which is used for detecting Fuel milestone
and iso build number from magnet link, so it can parse
links to images for "x.y.z" milestones.
Also modify default tests suite name (TestRail), because
it was decided to use separate suite for each milestone.

offer actionable information to developers or users. Ideally process
logs should be silent when idle, even in debug mode.

We use uWSGI mules for this task. This is because on scale lab we have timeout
errors which are reported like this:

Thus the idea to offload most of the work done in this handler to an
asynchronous worker (uWSGI mule in this case). Note that increasing uWSGI

commit_message:
ClusterChangesHandler task called asynchronously

We use uWSGI mules for this task. This is because on scale lab we have timeout
errors which are reported like this:

DEBUG - Uuuups https://bugs.launchpad.net/fuel/+bug/1384623 again

Thus the idea to offload most of the work done in this handler to an
asynchronous worker (uWSGI mule in this case). Note that increasing uWSGI
workers count doesn't help -- timeouts for this specific request will still
occur, we would only have the advantage of not blocking the API so much.

Other suggestions were made:
- use receiverd -- this has the disadvantage of breaking current flow of
  messages which is something like Nailgun -> Astute -> receiver
  (we would have in this case: Nailgun -> receiver -> Astute -> receiver
  which is not intuitive)
- use Celery -- this is a big change and not a bad idea for the future
  but we would like to have this merged for the 6.1 release, mules are at
  hand already
- performance improvements -- this is not that easy too (as noted in the
  blueprint 200-nodes-support)

blueprint: 200-nodes-support
Related-Bug: #1428957

Change-Id: Ib456efe434e956adfca7d20eb4a831e1c6102342

commit_message:
DiskFile refactoring to per-policy classes

Refactors diskfile.py to implement policy-type-specific
diskfile behavior in diskfile (sub-)classes.

This patch creates policy type specific diskfile
classes to allow some inheritance and overriding
of get_ondisk_files and hash_cleanup_listdir.

Also moves the file name mangling methods
from storage_policy.py to diskfile.py (ts_to_fname
and fname_to_ts). IMHO that is the right place for them
since they are diskfile-implementation choices and the new
classes added provide a better home for them.

Change-Id: I303e8551de98301c0fcb154a5ba392034046d72a

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-03-23 16:02:46.000000000', 'files': ['lib/astute/orchestrator.rb'], 'message': 'Don't use execute_tasks for pre_provision tasks

The `execute_tasks` method was designed to execute some abstract tasks
sent by Nailgun. Hence, in the end of execution if all is ok it sends
the "ready" status back to Nailgun. It's wrong in case of pre_provision
tasks, because they don't mean provisioning is done.

'}]
commit_message:
Don't use execute_tasks for pre_provision tasks

The `execute_tasks` method was designed to execute some abstract tasks
sent by Nailgun. Hence, in the end of execution if all is ok it sends
the "ready" status back to Nailgun. It's wrong in case of pre_provision
tasks, because they don't mean provisioning is done.

Since this commit we're running pre_provision tasks by means Nailgun
Hooks and therefore do not report "ready" when they are done.

Closes-Bug: #1433060
Change-Id: I9d0cf11b1788c85937b5a15e44fc904cb24efbe3

commit_message:
Disable -dibtest jobs

The -dibtest jobs are experimental jobs against devstack-gate to test
dib images for trusty and precise as we bring those images up in new
regions. We are not currently able to bring those images up in rackspace
and we need to free up some disk space on the nodepool server so we are
cleaning up those images. To prevent zuul from getting cranky we also
remove the jobs that use these images from zuul.

Change-Id: I91f8d91318752e09a15d64c8b3c506cf83badca2

commit_message:
Bump cryptography version to latest

The newer version of cryptography includes convenience functions
to serialize RSA keys which is useful for keystone and potentially
other projects.

Keystone Fernet tokens (one of the most requested features
for keystone) do not work until 0.7. 

Required for Id18fe9f8488204e73d063d7771357eced82e441f

Change-Id: I98941cce82d3c33bcc95ecc48ecff413ef81664a

commit_message:
re-add pacemaker configuration system (pcs)

The python-pcs package is the packet construction set [1]. This package
has been shipped with Debian/Ubuntu for quite a long time. For some
reason the pacemaker/corosync configuration system [2] has been packaged
for Ubuntu under the name `python-pcs'. Use the correct name (that is,
`pcs', like its RPM counterpart) to resolve the collision.

[1] https://github.com/gvnn3/PCS
[2] https://github.com/feist/pcs


blueprint support-ubuntu-trusty

Change-Id: I7291aff00de3a69add5a2ce1b4edff3bd33c1ba8
Signed-off-by: Sergii Golovatiuk <sgolovatiuk@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
WIP: Move triggers from assembly to plan

The high points:
- Moved trigger_id from assembly to plan in datamodels
- Added an internal method to find assemblies by plan
- Moved trigger_uri generation to plan
- Moved trust_id from assembly to plan in datamodels
- Renamed tools/trigger-assembly.py to trigger-app.py
- Deploy, if successful, should destroy (soon, just shutdown)
  other assemblies

The low points:
- ED WHERE ARE YOUR TESTS MAN NOTHING WORKS
- SERIOUSLY YOU DIDN'T EVEN TOUCH THE TESTS
- shell_nobuild doesn't use deployer, so deployer doesn't
  remove old assemblies
- A lot of code was shamelessly teleported to plan_handler
  from assembly_handler, mostly to reduce the complexity of
  these changes. See how well that worked!
- Yes, plan_handler makes use of an assembly_handler. I'm not
  sure if that's the best way to do it, but it's worked well
  enough for most of my attempts!

Change-Id: Ia48f95f7f9def4b473cd51df80554688ae287fa3

commit_message:
Add sanity check for OVSDB native support

This check has specific warnings about the need to install the
python-openvswitch package to use OVSDB native. If an unknown
Exception is thrown when doing a simple get_bridges() call, it will
also fail, logging the exception.

Partially-Implements: blueprint vsctl-to-ovsdb
Change-Id: Ibd2dac02c5a93bb391b620cc27bc46a6cdf6d817

commit_message:
Document requirement of cryptography>=0.7

Fernet tokens are built on features in cryptography 0.7. This is noted by the
fact we pull in cryptography 0.8 from global requirements, but this commit
adds a documentation warning as well.

commit_message:
keep interface_properties on NIC update

interface_properties should be kept on NIC update when no new values were provided.
Nailgun agent updates data this way.
interface_properties should be set to defaults for new interfaces only.

Closes-Bug: #1433486
Change-Id: I7e0ac88dde09f6eb28ed7079b3e3a15689da466e

revisions:
[{'number': 10, 'created': '2015-03-05 14:07:09.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_db/sqlalchemy/utils.py', 'oslo_db/sqlalchemy/update_match.py', 'oslo_db/tests/sqlalchemy/test_update_match.py', 'oslo_db/sqlalchemy/session.py'], 'message': "Implement generic update-on-match feature

This feature provides the query.update_on_match()
and query.update_returning_pk() methods, as well
as the manufacture_persistent_object(),
manufacture_entity_criteria(), and manufacture_criteria()
utility functions.

query.update_on_match() is used to UPDATE a row based on a variety
of criteria, and to then return a fully persistent object
state representing the row that was matched.  It
essentially intends to provide an UPDATE that is guaranteed
to have matched a specific row in the presence of potential
race conditions without using any locking, and to then
return a record of that row as if it had been SELECTed.

query.update_returning_pk() is a public method that
also serves as part of the implementation of
query.update_on_match(); this method delivers an UPDATE
statement such that the primary key of the single row
matched is returned; if zero or multiple rows are matched,
and error is raised.   To handle this, several backend-specific
strategies are provided, which are automatically selected
based on the best available.  The lowest strategy
performs a re-SELECT, but still assumes there's
a simple unique column to be queried on, as is currently the
use case in Nova (uuid is present).  On Postgresql, MySQL
and other databases besides SQLite and possibly DB2, more
atomic strategies are used.

Change-Id: I059f4ae6e72cfa6681a179314144214639f283ef
"}]
commit_message:
Implement generic update-on-match feature

This feature provides the query.update_on_match()
and query.update_returning_pk() methods, as well
as the manufacture_persistent_object(),
manufacture_entity_criteria(), and manufacture_criteria()
utility functions.

query.update_on_match() is used to UPDATE a row based on a variety
of criteria, and to then return a fully persistent object
state representing the row that was matched.  It
essentially intends to provide an UPDATE that is guaranteed
to have matched a specific row in the presence of potential
race conditions without using any locking, and to then
return a record of that row as if it had been SELECTed.

query.update_returning_pk() is a public method that
also serves as part of the implementation of
query.update_on_match(); this method delivers an UPDATE
statement such that the primary key of the single row
matched is returned; if zero or multiple rows are matched,
and error is raised.   To handle this, several backend-specific
strategies are provided, which are automatically selected
based on the best available.  The lowest strategy
performs a re-SELECT, but still assumes there's
a simple unique column to be queried on, as is currently the
use case in Nova (uuid is present).  On Postgresql, MySQL
and other databases besides SQLite and possibly DB2, more
atomic strategies are used.

Change-Id: I059f4ae6e72cfa6681a179314144214639f283ef

commit_message:
Pass $ceilometer to openstack::glance and openstack::controller

Commit I00db51ceb4121e73bfe7e256b895e4fae122a496 added possibility to
control whether Ceilometer notifications are sent, but didn't add
appropriate parameter to higher level classes, making notifications
disabled even if Ceilometer is enabled.

Additionally backport I3f2c29adbfb605ef288962f72ba81c11811cb357 to
glance module.

Change-Id: I2db7c13cd9c59e29e42e5000961eeedc6717e1ee
Closes-Bug: 1433075
Related-Bug: 1425982

This fixes a bug where if a file was skipped, it still showed in
the total listing of files, and so it could be associated with the
score of a non-skipped file. To fix these, when a file is skipped
we also remove it from the list of files in scope.

Change-Id: Ifdfe64b5720e1f809385140960b7b2c1d2238a92
Closes-Bug: #1434659
'}]
commit_message:
Fixing a bug with files listing when a file was skipped

This fixes a bug where if a file was skipped, it still showed in
the total listing of files, and so it could be associated with the
score of a non-skipped file. To fix these, when a file is skipped
we also remove it from the list of files in scope.

Change-Id: Ifdfe64b5720e1f809385140960b7b2c1d2238a92
Closes-Bug: #1434659

Patch 4: even more typos

commit_message:
Send notification to controller about HA router state change

The L3 agent gets keepalived state change notifications via
a unix domain socket. These events are now batched and
send out as a single RPC to the server. In case the same
router got updated multiple times during the batch period,
only the latest state is sent.

Partially-Implements: blueprint report-ha-router-master
Change-Id: I36834ad3d9e8a49a702f01acc29c7c38f2d48833

commit_message:
Properly handle embedded newlines in csv

When parsing the response from the OpenStack client values (like
keystone tenant descriptions) can have embedded newline. To avoid this
issue, we drop lines that don't start with a double quoted value until
the first one we find.

(cherry picked from stackforge/puppet-openstacklib,
from commit efa9181201d33a6bcc4dbe0a482a5d213b6fb5fd)
Change-Id: Ie952161b503d2c46637e6a6e1c83b2dfce1c03a7

revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2015-03-20 16:14:46.000000000', 'files': ['test/unit/common/test_storage_policy.py', 'test/functional/__init__.py', 'swift/common/storage_policy.py', 'doc/source/development_guidelines.rst'], 'message': "Enable in-process functional test policy to be configured

Currently the in-process tests build a 2 replica, 4 partition,
2 device object ring. This patch allows an alternative policy
and ring to be specified for testing via environment variables
that may optionally be set.

SWIFT_TEST_IN_PROCESS_CONF_DIR - This points the test setup to a
  directory which may have a swift.conf file and ring file. The
  test setup will then prefer these conf files over the samples
  in '/etc'.

SWIFT_TEST_POLICY - This causes the in-process test to
  use the specified policy from the swift.conf file and its
  associated ring for testing (first copying the conf and ring file
  and modifying device parameters to suit in-process testing). If
  not set, the tests will use the default policy.

The in-process tests now start sufficient object servers for the
ring file being tested against.

This should allow in-process functional testing of various policies
and rings (e.g. EC policies) without needing to reconfigure an SAIO
for each test scenario.

The refactoring of the in_process test setup code should also
allow easier addition of other 'hard-coded' test policies/rings
in the future.

Change-Id: I24f5a13de3d296b400da1691dcb53423a9f8a463
"}]
commit_message:
Enable in-process functional test policy to be configured

Currently the in-process tests build a 2 replica, 4 partition,
2 device object ring. This patch allows an alternative policy
and ring to be specified for testing via environment variables
that may optionally be set.

SWIFT_TEST_IN_PROCESS_CONF_DIR - This points the test setup to a
  directory which may have a swift.conf file and ring file. The
  test setup will then prefer these conf files over the samples
  in '/etc'.

SWIFT_TEST_POLICY - This causes the in-process test to
  use the specified policy from the swift.conf file and its
  associated ring for testing (first copying the conf and ring file
  and modifying device parameters to suit in-process testing). If
  not set, the tests will use the default policy.

The in-process tests now start sufficient object servers for the
ring file being tested against.

This should allow in-process functional testing of various policies
and rings (e.g. EC policies) without needing to reconfigure an SAIO
for each test scenario.

The refactoring of the in_process test setup code should also
allow easier addition of other 'hard-coded' test policies/rings
in the future.

Change-Id: I24f5a13de3d296b400da1691dcb53423a9f8a463

revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-03-20 13:21:34.000000000', 'files': ['ironic/tests/api/v1/test_nodes.py', 'ironic/api/controllers/v1/node.py'], 'message': 'Hide new fields via single method

With the introduction of microversions, node fields that are added in
a particular (micro)version should not be made visible to requests
for older versions. This patch puts the logic for handling this for
all such new fields in one method: hide_fields_in_newer_versions().

This should make it easier for developers to know where to add code,
and will (hopefully) prevent multiple methods from popping up for
each new set of fields.

This also removes the exception handling in allow_logical_names()
because it is not needed, since it is no longer being called in a
method where a pecan.request might not be available (eg, when
generating a sample of a Node for the documentation).

Change-Id: Id6aeb3543d447113a8cf702f2e85d8a9ca3858f3
'}]
commit_message:
Hide new fields via single method

With the introduction of microversions, node fields that are added in
a particular (micro)version should not be made visible to requests
for older versions. This patch puts the logic for handling this for
all such new fields in one method: hide_fields_in_newer_versions().

This should make it easier for developers to know where to add code,
and will (hopefully) prevent multiple methods from popping up for
each new set of fields.

This also removes the exception handling in allow_logical_names()
because it is not needed, since it is no longer being called in a
method where a pecan.request might not be available (eg, when
generating a sample of a Node for the documentation).

commit_message:
Fix common misspellings

Wikipedia's list of common misspellings [1] has a machine-readable
version.  This patch fixes those misspellings mentioned in the list
which don't have multiple right variants (as e.g. "accension", which can
be both "accession" and "ascension"), such misspellings are left
untouched.  The list of changes was manually re-checked for false
positives.

[1] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Lists_of_common_misspellings/For_machines

Change-Id: I52a6f641a203185f9005bc0731d15166ad741161
Signed-off-by: Martin Kletzander <mkletzan@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Func tests use fedora-heat-test-image

This runs the existing functional tests using the images built in
http://tarballs.openstack.org/heat-test-image/

This image should be a suitable alternative to
Fedora-x86_64-20-20140618-sda, with the extra benefit that it is
prepared to install the heat config agent projects during boot
so that test_server_software_config can be enabled.

This will also allow devstack to no longer load
Fedora-x86_64-20-20140618-sda onto the nodepool images which will reduce
gate resource consumption.

Change-Id: I6041b8d6e7e9422f6e220d7aef0ca38857085e4b

Add first test for patching environment, which

Additional variables required by patching tests:
 * PATCHING_MIRRORS - list of repositories with patched

'}]
commit_message:
Create tests for patching feature

Add first test for patching environment, which
deploys some cluster and apply patches on it.
Environment configuration (deployment test) is chosen
automatically based on packages tags.
Tests require errata.yaml which should include scenarios
for applying/verifying patches.
Additional variables required by patching tests:
 * PATCHING_MIRRORS - list of repositories with patched
   packages;
 * PATCHING_WEB_DIR - directory on master node which is
   available via HTTP (used for new repository);
 * PATCHING_BUG_ID - bug ID which is going to be fixed;
 * PATCHING_PKGS_TESTS - local path or URL to destination
   where test plans for packages are stored;
 * PATCHING_APPLY_TESTS - local path or URL which should
   be used to get test plans for bugs (using bug ID);
 * PATCHING_PKGS - list of patched packages; if empty -
   list is gotten from test plan (errata.yaml) or from
   repository.

Implements: blueprint mos-patching-tests

Change-Id: Ic696a49bd12504c9e045cf824248ff09bb7d53cb

commit_message:
Specify time units for default_lock_timeout

Currently, the docstring and sample config entries for
default_lock_timeout do not specify what units of time the value uses
(minutes, seconds, microseconds, etc).  This patch adds units to make
the value easier to understand for operators.

Closes-Bug: #1434620
DocImpact

commit_message:
Per-policy DiskFile classes

Adds specific disk file classes for EC policy types.

The new ECDiskFile and ECDiskFileWriter classes are used
by the ECDiskFileManager.

ECDiskFileManager is registered with the DiskFileRouter for
use with EC_POLICY type policies.

Updated -n processing. -n now specifies the maximum code lines

commit_message:
Fixed -n flag processing

Updated -n processing. -n now specifies the maximum code lines
to display for issues (in cases where statements cover many multiple
lines). -n now correctly limits line output to the specified value.
The default behaviour is to display all lines. A value of 0 suppresses
all code output.

Closes-bug: #1434283
Change-Id: I6aa7814f073d012029bda7783fa73746a56c2f5e

This patch implements the following changes:

'commit_aio' tests are now called 'scenario' tests
 - this is now set as the default test set

'commit_multinode' tests are now called 'api' tests
 - network, compute, object_storage tests have been added

'nightly_heat_multinode' tests are now called 'smoke' tests

commit_message:
Warn about deleting from DB node that is not offline

The --force parameter can be used to force the removal. Otherwise error is
printed and script exits without doing anything.

Usage:

fuel node --node-id 1 2 --delete-from-db

fuel node --node-id 1 --delete-from-db --force

Also, fixed illogical use of check_errors in run_cli_command function.

Implements blueprint node-removal-task

Closes-Bug: #1435281
Change-Id: I0c9e27450c09eb7ea6224ffc30c9284427cd5d1c

commit_message:
Add usages of plugin poll - part 2

It's required to add support of plugin poll in
plugin, so it's require big changes. We would do it
in series of small CR.

This part adds usages in CDH, vanilla 2

partially implements bp: add-timeouts-for-polling

Change-Id: Id3408c1a74c03efb8c05cc9d7cf75ebddbbcb531

commit_message:
Install MySQL JDBC driver along with client

Oozie can't start properly because of absence of MySQL JDBC driver in
its lib/ directory. The jar is copied there from /usr/share/java/mysql-
connector-java.jar during Oozie install. Driver is provided by
libmysql-java on Ubuntu and mysql-connector-java on RedHat and SLES

Change-Id: I75d70eea82ec136f49770431a1d0a872717263e1
Closes-Bug: #1432633

commit_message:
Add usages of plugin poll - part 1

It's required to add support of plugin poll in
plugin, so it's require big changes. We would do it
in series of small CR.

This patch introduce support in vanilla 1 and in hdp.

partially implements bp: add-timeouts-for-polling

Change-Id: I46e277beabe00f8d18b2370065dc07c39a63f1bd

commit_message:
Support local bundles

If the bundle is being installed from a local file
first attempt to search for files in the folder, relatvie
to the directory of the bundle, next check the URL attribute and
finally check repository. Same for requirements and images.

Change-Id: I8a40ad274e60d97111602bdd0d7b08eb39126a6d

commit_message:
Fix order of arguments in assertEqual - Part3

This part contains changes in tests of service.

Some tests used incorrect order assertEqual(observed, expected).
The correct order expected by testtools is:
    def assertEqual(self, expected, observed, message='')

It requires big changes and some tests change frequently.
So I would do it in series of small CR, and this is the last one.

Closes-Bug: #1259292

Change-Id: I20c215da18775e9a4d257462446f4adbecd26056

commit_message:
Add support for show_events parameter

Cluster get operation now supports show_events flag to display provision
progress.
Removed events endpoint as it is going to be removed from the API.

Partially implements bp: event-log

Change-Id: I6892c8be2f8daaa215732f5e58524620cb9a1f85

commit_message:
Fix order of arguments in assertEqual - Part1

Some tests used incorrect order assertEqual(observed, expected).
The correct order expected by testtools is:
    def assertEqual(self, expected, observed, message='')
Changed to use the right order. Also if the order is wrong and
expected value is None, change it to assertIsNone instead.

It requires big changes and some tests change frequently.
So I would do it in series of small CR.
This part contains all changes except tests of plugins and service.

Partial-Bug: #1259292

Change-Id: Iefbb5f4b9efca35f7a2298f9f7f5b9de73fc260f

Because yaql 0.2.x doesn't support unary operators it is necessary
to write 0-1 instead of -1

* For other drivers it's assumed that at least READ_COMMITTED

commit_message:
Implementing 'acquire_lock' method and fixing workflow completion

* For sqlite it's based on eventlet semaphores
* For other drivers it's assumed that at least READ_COMMITTED
  transactions are used
* Engine method on_action_complete() now acquires lock on
  workflow execution object to prevent incorrect concurrent
  access causing problems in 'join' and 'timeout' policy

Change-Id: I80bc317de4bfd2547f8529d8f2b3238a004d7522

commit_message:
Properly handle embedded newlines in csv

When parsing the response from the OpenStack client values (like
keystone tenant descriptions) can have embedded newline. To avoid this
issue, we drop lines that don't start with a double quoted value until
the first one we find.

This patch is manually pick from https://review.openstack.org/#/c/164929/

Change-Id: Ib24070fc6f0e772c986ae22f8599b4eb2b44bc89

When configured to use sentinel with the redis driver, allow the
redis-py client to manage the connection to the currently elected
master.

'master_for' will return a StricRedis client which is bound to a
connection pool that queries the Sentinel[s] when providing
connections from the pool.

This means that failover handling is automatic as long as the

Closes-Bug: #1434043
"}]
commit_message:
Use a sentinel connection pool to manage failover

When configured to use sentinel with the redis driver, allow the
redis-py client to manage the connection to the currently elected
master.

'master_for' will return a StricRedis client which is bound to a
connection pool that queries the Sentinel[s] when providing
connections from the pool.

This means that failover handling is automatic as long as the
sentinels can be reached and they have elected a new master.

Change-Id: I8fd672e664d98097944a7c984cadab5fb08dd2d6
Closes-Bug: #1434043

commit_message:
iniset heat_integrationtests.conf

This change adds a prepare_test_env.sh script which builds a
heat_integrationtests.conf using the iniset function from devstack.

prepare_test_env.sh can be run locally with appropriate credentials
and a valid $DEST. In the gate post_test_hook.sh runs prepare_test_env.sh
with sudo so it has the required permissions to write
heat_integrationtests.conf.

Instead of adding more environment variables which are used as default
config options, replace those by actually writing out a
heat_integrationtests.conf file with the required values. This was always
the original intention - it just hadn't been done yet.

The exception to this is the sourced auth environment variables which
are very convenient to not have to state explicitly in the config file.

Change-Id: Ibdba20172964cb5c9e33071cf346d7e0315aea6c

commit_message:
Second round of cleansing of the exception module

This patch removes some exception classes and makes some exception types
more specific:
- Removed ProjectNotMatch exception, which is not very useful;
- Removed ActionMissingTarget exception, which should be caught during
  parameter validation phase;
- Removed ActionMissingPolicy exception, which should be caught during
  parameter validation phase;
- Delete the generic 'NotFound' exception and make such kind of
  exceptions more specific.

Change-Id: Ief6ec5166844474f975f3d87a3a2fe5459b340d1

commit_message:
Refactor openflow app

- Move to a more pythonic, idiomatic, shorter style.
- Various lists (subnets, routers) kept adding multiple instances of the
  same entity instead of overriding the current configuration.
- Added accessors in the objects for common properties so that only
  objects are needed.

Change-Id: Ide85257debb5865078dcb2eb69c772ca92a0e61f
Signed-off-by: Saggi Mizrahi <saggi.mizrahi@huawei.com>

commit_message:
Disable registration on CentOS images

When building CentOS images, disable the image registration (usually
with subscription-manager, which is RHEL-only).

Due to a bug in diskimage-builder [1], we need to temporarly export
REG_HALT_UNREGISTER=1 to prevent unregistration too.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/162239/

Change-Id: I47d2c1f6576700d9eb56ecceac1e19c2b40e8297

commit_message:
Add hacking rule for baremetal client

There are many methods which get resource information on each client
and these method names are different like "get_<resource name>" or
"show_<resource name>".
The number of "get_<resource name>" is 124, and the one of "show_
<resource name>" is 12, so this patch adds a hacking rule to avoid
"show_<resource name>" methods. In addition, this patch applis the
rule to baremetal client only because of easy implementation/review.

Change-Id: I25fdce0791f05c4608628af4e8adaf8b284cbd03
